<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-02T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-02T18:00:00-05:00" n="221" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d221">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">840.50 UNRRA/11–2744: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the American Representative on the Advisory Council for
                                    Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-02T19:00:00-04:00">December 2, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>444. Department somewhat concerned over statement made by Jackson
                                (Caserta No. 1515, November 27—UNRRA from Jackson No. 95<note n="32a" xml:id="d221fn32a">Not printed.</note>) that continuance
                                of use of Swedish ships is not related to continuing <pb facs="0224" n="212" xml:id="pg_212"/> operations of Swedish-Swiss
                                Commission. As stated in our No. 33 to Athens<note n="33" xml:id="d221fn33">See footnote 25, <ref target="#pg_208">p.
                                        208</ref>.</note> the question of Swedish ships is now under
                                discussion with Swedish Government and it appears that continuance
                                of Swedish-Swiss Commission at least in &amp; nominal capacity may
                                be necessary in order to assure continued use of the ships. You will
                                be advised of any further developments.</p>
                            <p>Repeated to Athens.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>